  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The functional safety assessment considers the, confirmation plan, recommendations from previous functional safety&#xD;
    assessments (if available) and results from previous functional safety audits and confirmation reviews.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The conclusion of the functional safety assessment must include a recommendation for acceptance, conditional&#xD;
    acceptance, or rejection of the functional safety of the item.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The only condition under which conditional acceptance can be given is if the functional safety of the item is&#xD;
    considered evident despite the identified open issues. If this happens it is expected that any&amp;nbsp;corrective actions&#xD;
    listed in the functional safety assessment report, should be carried out.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If the item has been rejected then actions must be taken to correct the issue and the assessment repeated.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more details on the functional safety assessment report it is advised that the user refers to ISO 26262, Volume 2,&#xD;
    clause 6.4.6.7&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To plan the functional safety assessment for items with an ASIL of C or D; it is recommend for an item with an ASIL of B</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
